A small city in central Florida that doesn't really have a whole lot to offer for both tourists and residence alike. However, if you happen to be on Highway 50 heading towards Orlando or Brevard County, then by all means, I recommend you check out the Fort Christmas Historical Site.

Historical military fort built on December 25, 1837 during the Second Seminole War. Inside displays a wide variety of military and Seminole Indian artifacts.
Located just off State Road 50, 20 miles east of Orlando en route to Kennedy Space Center, Merritt Island National Wildlife Refuge, and Canaveral National Seashore in Titusville.
